---
description: Vitest testing patterns — LLM mocks, coverage config, test file structure
globs: src/**/__tests__/*.test.ts,src/test/**
alwaysApply: false
---
- All LLM calls globally mocked via `src/test/setup.ts` — no real API calls in tests
- Override per-test: `vi.spyOn(llm, 'llmCall').mockResolvedValue('...')`
- Coverage excludes: `src/test/`, `src/bin.ts`, `src/cli.ts`, `src/commands/**`, `dist/**`
- Scoring checks (`src/scoring/checks/`) are pure functions — test with temp dirs or mocked fs
- LLM utils (`extractJson`, `estimateTokens`) are pure — no mocking needed
- Fingerprint tests (`src/fingerprint/__tests__/`): mock `fs` and `child_process.execSync`
- Learner tests (`src/learner/__tests__/`): use temp directories from `os.tmpdir()`
- Use `memfs` for filesystem mocking when needed
- Run single file: `npx vitest run src/scoring/__tests__/accuracy.test.ts`
- Spawn mock return values must include `stderr: { on: vi.fn() }` when stdio is `['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe']`
- Tests for `src/llm/__tests__/index.test.ts` must call `vi.unmock('../index.js')` and `resetProvider()` in beforeEach
